                            "spans": [
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        443,
                                        2432,
                                        2106,
                                        2613
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": "In this paper, we argue that the prompt can be enhanced by continuously collecting the analysis of LLMs on those ineffective thoughts - wrong reasoning steps in a chain of thought. Therefore, even a simple prompt, such as "
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        443,
                                        2432,
                                        2106,
                                        2613
                                    ],
                                    "type": "inline_equation",
                                    "content": "\\mathbb{I}\\left(X, Q\\right)"
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        443,
                                        2432,
                                        2106,
                                        2613
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": ", potentially leading to ineffective thoughts, can be progressively refined by relying on such analysis to gain powerful thoughts toward the solution."
                                }
                            ]
                        }
                    ],
                    "index": 5
                },
                {
